Sentencas: CuFe0.8 (Fe:Cu = 0.8:1, atomic ratio) alloy layer is fabricated on both bare and pre-oxidized SUS 430 steels by direct current magnetron sputtering, followed by exposing at 800 degrees C in air to obtain a protective coating for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) steel interconnects.
Titulo: CuFe2O4/CuO coating for solid oxide fuel cell steel interconnects

Sentencas: The CuFe0.8 alloy layer is thermally converted to CuFe2O4/CuO coating, which effectively suppresses the out-migration of Cr. Pre-oxidation treatment not only initially accelerates the formation of CuFe2O4/CuO coating but also further inhibits the Cr and Fe outward diffusion.
Titulo: CuFe2O4/CuO coating for solid oxide fuel cell steel interconnects

Sentencas: Suppressing outward diffusion of Cr could improve electrical property of oxide scale and decrease the risk of cathode Cr-poisoning.
Titulo: CuFe2O4/CuO coating for solid oxide fuel cell steel interconnects

Sentencas: Blocking out-diffusion of Fe is beneficial to stabilize the CuO layer.
Titulo: CuFe2O4/CuO coating for solid oxide fuel cell steel interconnects

Sentencas: After 2520 h oxidation, the scale ASR at 800 degrees C is 66.9 mU cm(2) for coated bare steel, 43.4 mU cm(2) for the coated pre-oxidized steel.
Titulo: CuFe2O4/CuO coating for solid oxide fuel cell steel interconnects
